Class PlainParamValueProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.linuxforhealth.fhir.persistence.params.database.PlainParamValueProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParamValueProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PlainDerbyParamValueProcessor, PlainPostgresParamValueProcessor
    public abstract class PlainParamValueProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IParamValueProcessor
    Loads search parameter values into the target PostgreSQL database using the plain (non-sharded) schema variant.

        protected void addMissingCodeSystems​(java.util.List<CodeSystemValue> missing)
                              throws FHIRPersistenceException
        These code systems weren't found in the database, so we need to try and add them. We have to deal with concurrency here - there's a chance another thread could also be trying to add them. To avoid deadlocks, it's important to do any inserts in a consistent order. At the end, we should be able to read back values for each entry

        Make sure we have values for all the logical_resource_ident values we have collected in the current batch. Need to make sure these are added in order to minimize deadlocks. Note that because we may create new logical_resource_ident records, we could be blocked by the main add_any_resource procedure run within the server CREATE/UPDATE
